# kerf.box — environment configuration
#
# Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) and fill in what you need. kerf.box is
# account-free: there is NO auth and NO database to configure. With NONE of
# these set it still boots and serves demo content with an in-memory rate
# limiter; callers bring their own AI provider key (BYOK) for live inference
# — Anthropic, OpenAI, Gemini, Kimi, Qwen, DeepSeek, Groq, OpenRouter,
# Ollama, or any custom OpenAI-compatible endpoint.
# In production, set these in your host's env (e.g. Vercel project settings)
# — never commit real secrets.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Inference (Anthropic)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OPTIONAL server-side key for live research + copy generation. Leave blank
# and the hosted model is BYOK-only: every live call must carry the caller's
# own key in the X-Provider + X-Api-Key headers (or the legacy
# X-Anthropic-Key shorthand) — never stored or logged — and demo content is
# served when no key is present. Set this only if you're self-hosting and
# want the instance to run inference on its own key. The server-side
# fallback is Anthropic-only by design; other providers are BYOK-per-request.
# KERFBOX_ANTHROPIC_KEY is preferred (namespaced, can't collide with other
# tools that auto-read ANTHROPIC_API_KEY); the bare name works as a fallback.
# KERFBOX_ANTHROPIC_KEY=sk-ant-...
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
#
# Optional model overrides.
# KERFBOX_STRATEGY_MODEL=
# KERFBOX_COPY_MODEL=

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Rate limiting (Upstash Redis or Vercel KV) — OPTIONAL
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The API is open and rate-limited per IP. Without these, limiting is
# in-memory per-instance. Set one pair for a durable, cross-instance limiter.
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=
# KV_REST_API_URL=
# KV_REST_API_TOKEN=

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Site
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Canonical origin for metadata/sitemap/OG. Set to your deployment's URL.
# Defaults to https://kerfbox.vercel.app when unset.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://kerfbox.vercel.app
